The Stockholm bourse authorities saidthey were to extend trading on the exchange by 30 minutes until1500 (1400 GMT) because the afternoon call took longer thannormal due to hectic selling pressure.    A spokeswoman told Reuters the measure was purelyadministrative and aimed at allowing the bourse time to processdeals in exceptionally heavy turnover of around 590 mln crowns.    "It was necessary to extend trading hours as the call-overwent on beyond two o'clock," she said. REUTER&#3;